1
00:00:10,100 --> 00:00:12,333
<i>Hello, Jeff?
I have a favor to ask.</i>

2
00:00:12,467 --> 00:00:15,067
<i>But don't tell your siblings,
especially your mom.</i>

3
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:17,433
<i>Why is Dad looking
for a psychic?</i>

4
00:00:17,567 --> 00:00:20,867
<i>Mom, is it okay if we speak
with a psychic?</i>

5
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,067
<i> I don't need a psychic.</i>

6
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:23,333
<i>No one's putting a curse on me.</i>

7
00:00:23,467 --> 00:00:24,867
<i> Aren't we talking about Dad?</i>

8
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,033
<i> Manuel, who's that?</i>

9
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:28,733
<i>She's the psychic that
Jeffrey's friend knows.</i>

10
00:00:28,867 --> 00:00:30,100
<i> You know many things.</i>

11
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:32,100
<i> Secrets that aren't yours.</i>

12
00:00:32,233 --> 00:00:33,767
<i> Come in, Miss Precy.</i>

13
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:45,467
So, what happened
to your daughter?

14
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:48,467
She had a car accident.

15
00:00:49,467 --> 00:00:51,167
When did this happen?

16
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:54,267
Two weeks ago.

17
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:55,333
And then...

18
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:59,133
I always dream of her.

19
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:01,900
She's telling me something.

20
00:01:02,033 --> 00:01:04,500
Which I don't understand.

21
00:01:04,633 --> 00:01:07,300
I couldn't stop Manuel, friend.

22
00:01:07,467 --> 00:01:10,200
- I'm sorry.
- Alice, come on.

23
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:12,500
Just let Manuel be with whatever
trip he's on.

24
00:01:12,633 --> 00:01:13,667
Let him do his nonsense.

25
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:14,700
He'll stop eventually.

26
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:16,100
What nonsense
are you talking about?

27
00:01:16,233 --> 00:01:18,700
Aren't you scared he'll end up
talking to Jessica?

28
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:20,600
And that your daughter might
tell the truth?

29
00:01:20,733 --> 00:01:22,633
Don't tell me you believe
such things?

30
00:01:22,767 --> 00:01:26,200
My mom's cousin is an albularyo,
a folk healer.

31
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:28,500
So yes, I believe
in these things.

32
00:01:28,633 --> 00:01:29,533
Come on.

33
00:01:29,667 --> 00:01:31,033
They're just scammers.

34
00:01:31,167 --> 00:01:32,867
Hazel, no,
I'm telling you.

35
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,733
<i> Please, Alice. Stop.</i>

36
00:01:34,867 --> 00:01:36,267
If you really believe
in such things,

37
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:38,867
then send that woman away.

38
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:41,067
I'm giving you permission
to do that.

39
00:01:41,233 --> 00:01:42,433
Take care of Manuel for now.

40
00:01:42,567 --> 00:01:44,233
I'll be back tomorrow.

41
00:01:44,367 --> 00:01:46,033
- Bye.
- Hazel...

42
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:53,567
Hazel, come on.

43
00:02:13,733 --> 00:02:18,133
Close your eyes
and listen to me.

44
00:02:19,267 --> 00:02:25,767
Don't use your ears,
use your heart instead.

45
00:02:35,367 --> 00:02:39,300
She misses you
and you want to know...

46
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:44,100
why you keep dreaming
the same thing.

47
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:49,000
You want to know what
she wants to tell you.

48
00:02:51,633 --> 00:02:52,733
Is that right?

49
00:02:53,867 --> 00:02:55,200
Yes.

50
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:06,067
She misses talking with you
every night

51
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:07,567
before going to sleep.

52
00:03:09,933 --> 00:03:13,533
Her favorite dish that
you often used to cook...

53
00:03:13,667 --> 00:03:16,767
- Even the food?
- is Afritada.

54
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:17,967
How did she know that?

55
00:03:19,100 --> 00:03:20,200
Where is this?

56
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,767
It's not here
in the Philippines.

57
00:03:26,367 --> 00:03:28,300
Is it abroad?

58
00:03:28,433 --> 00:03:31,600
Yes, that's in Canada.

59
00:03:31,733 --> 00:03:33,533
When we came home
to the Philippines,

60
00:03:33,667 --> 00:03:35,167
I could no longer
cook for her.

61
00:03:36,333 --> 00:03:38,467
And now she's worried about...

62
00:03:39,767 --> 00:03:43,133
who's massaging your feet.

63
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:48,833
Hazel, answer the call, please.

64
00:03:48,967 --> 00:03:51,433
Hazel, take the call.

65
00:03:55,267 --> 00:03:57,533
Hello! How are you?

66
00:03:59,467 --> 00:04:00,667
I'm okay.

67
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:02,200
I'm doing well.

68
00:04:02,333 --> 00:04:04,467
I'm so glad to hear about it.

69
00:04:06,133 --> 00:04:07,933
I wish you were here, Daddy.

70
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:11,833
- You know,
- Is this true?

71
00:04:11,967 --> 00:04:14,700
everything is so beautiful here.

72
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:17,933
You'll enjoy it here.

73
00:04:21,233 --> 00:04:23,200
Here, there is no more pain.

74
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,200
Everything is perfect here.

75
00:04:28,233 --> 00:04:31,300
And Daddy,
you will walk again here.

76
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:35,767
I'm so excited
to walk with you again.

77
00:04:38,567 --> 00:04:40,600
But it's not your time yet.

78
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:02,067
<i> Love you, Dad.</i>

79
00:05:02,233 --> 00:05:03,233
Jessica?

80
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:05,500
Jessica, dear.

81
00:05:07,867 --> 00:05:09,467
Dear...

82
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:14,067
When you appear in my dreams...

83
00:05:15,133 --> 00:05:17,400
asking me to forgive you

84
00:05:17,533 --> 00:05:18,500
and your mother...

85
00:05:19,533 --> 00:05:21,433
Dear, what is that
supposed to mean?

86
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:25,900
I hope you
don't see me differently

87
00:05:27,433 --> 00:05:29,533
when you know the truth.

88
00:05:29,667 --> 00:05:30,667
No, dear.

89
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,667
Tell me the truth.

90
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,433
What is the truth?

91
00:05:41,167 --> 00:05:44,633
Dear... Dear, tell me the truth.

92
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:48,867
The truth...

93
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,333
is I'm not...

94
00:05:51,467 --> 00:05:52,667
That's enough!

95
00:05:54,967 --> 00:05:56,467
Alice.

96
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:58,067
Stop fooling Manuel!

97
00:05:58,200 --> 00:05:59,067
Alice!

98
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:00,767
Get out of here!

99
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:01,967
Alice, what are you doing?

100
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:04,100
Stop using Jessica's memories!

101
00:06:04,233 --> 00:06:05,167
- My godchild!
- Alice!

102
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:07,333
-Leave! She's no longer with us!
-Alice!

103
00:06:09,167 --> 00:06:11,367
Leave! Please!
Go on!

104
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:12,433
Leave!

105
00:06:12,567 --> 00:06:13,533
Alice!

106
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:18,700
You're rude!

107
00:06:18,833 --> 00:06:21,033
You have no right
to send my guest away!

108
00:06:21,167 --> 00:06:22,900
Get mad if you want, Manuel!

109
00:06:23,033 --> 00:06:24,800
I'm just protecting you!

110
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:25,967
She's fooling you!

111
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:27,567
No, Alice!

112
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,267
Fine, you tell me.

113
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:31,000
How did she know Jessica's
favorite food?

114
00:06:31,133 --> 00:06:33,300
And that we talk
before we go to bed?

115
00:06:33,433 --> 00:06:35,500
And Jessica massages my feet?

116
00:06:35,633 --> 00:06:37,400
How did she know all of that?
Tell me!

117
00:06:37,533 --> 00:06:38,667
All of those

118
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:41,833
are in Jessica's
FriendsBook page, Manuel.

119
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:43,600
For sure, that old woman
did her research

120
00:06:43,733 --> 00:06:45,600
to get money from you.

121
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:48,267
Did you know what she was doing

122
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:49,900
when your eyes were closed?

123
00:06:50,033 --> 00:06:52,233
And she pretended to be Jessica?

124
00:06:52,367 --> 00:06:54,167
She was trying to stop herself
from laughing.

125
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:58,433
Because she knew
you were so convinced.

126
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:03,167
Manuel, she's the one
who's rude.

127
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:06,733
She disrespected
Jessica's memories.

128
00:07:08,067 --> 00:07:09,367
Sorry, but...

129
00:07:10,867 --> 00:07:15,100
I won't let anyone disrespect
my goddaughter.

130
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:20,300
I want to talk to my daughter.

131
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:24,133
Alice, I want to talk
to Jessica!

132
00:07:24,267 --> 00:07:25,767
Manuel, she's gone.

133
00:07:27,433 --> 00:07:28,867
She's now in heaven.

134
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:31,267
Let go of her.

135
00:07:32,333 --> 00:07:35,033
But if something
is still bothering you,

136
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:38,533
I'll let you talk
someone I know.

137
00:07:39,633 --> 00:07:42,400
Someone who's not a scammer.

138
00:07:42,533 --> 00:07:44,433
Someone who's not
after your money.

139
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:19,967
Jessica.

140
00:08:22,567 --> 00:08:24,400
- Jessica.
- Sweetie?

141
00:08:25,867 --> 00:08:27,167
Jessica...

142
00:08:29,033 --> 00:08:31,000
- Jessica!
- Sweetie?

143
00:08:34,867 --> 00:08:36,333
- Sweetie!
- Oh?

144
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:38,700
Mom, I dreamed of Jessica.

145
00:08:39,767 --> 00:08:41,100
Was it like before?

146
00:08:41,233 --> 00:08:44,500
The one where you're pulling
each other?

147
00:08:44,633 --> 00:08:45,633
Yes, Mom.

148
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:50,533
But this time it was different.

149
00:08:52,767 --> 00:08:54,567
I didn't let go of her.

150
00:08:56,233 --> 00:08:58,000
She didn't get hit by a car.

151
00:08:59,233 --> 00:09:01,733
Mom, I was able to say
sorry to her.

152
00:09:03,533 --> 00:09:05,767
And she forgave me.

153
00:09:14,467 --> 00:09:17,667
I wish my dream was real.

154
00:09:20,167 --> 00:09:22,633
I wish Jessica was still alive.

155
00:09:23,533 --> 00:09:26,067
I wish she was with us
right now.

156
00:09:45,333 --> 00:09:46,333
Manuel.

157
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,633
Manuel.

158
00:09:48,767 --> 00:09:51,500
this is Pastor Ishmael Laurente.

159
00:09:52,533 --> 00:09:55,767
I brought him here to talk
to you about

160
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:58,100
what you're feeling about
your dreams of Jessica.

161
00:09:58,233 --> 00:09:59,967
So you can find some peace.

162
00:10:01,633 --> 00:10:03,667
Pastor Ishma, this is Manuel.

163
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:07,100
A blessed day to you, Manuel.

164
00:10:46,567 --> 00:10:48,233
Mom, food's ready.

165
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,967
Mom, are you okay?

166
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:56,833
You've been in there
for a while.

167
00:10:59,733 --> 00:11:02,200
It's just that...

168
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:04,167
my stomach hurts a bit.

169
00:11:05,333 --> 00:11:06,300
Okay.

170
00:11:06,433 --> 00:11:08,133
Just come out when you're ready,
Mom, all right?

171
00:11:50,133 --> 00:11:51,867
<i> We can run some tests.</i>

172
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:56,433
<i>It's not normal to faint
just because of a headache.</i>

173
00:11:56,567 --> 00:11:58,900
<i>Oh my, it's been happening
more often, Ma'am.</i>

174
00:11:59,033 --> 00:12:00,533
<i> I'm starting to get worried.</i>

175
00:12:00,667 --> 00:12:02,500
<i>Why don't you reconsider
doctor's advice</i>

176
00:12:02,633 --> 00:12:04,733
<i>so we can find out
what's causing it?</i>

177
00:12:04,867 --> 00:12:06,133
<i> Your moods keep changing.</i>

178
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:08,300
<i> You're forgetful, too.</i>

179
00:12:08,433 --> 00:12:10,467
<i>Sometimes you just stare off,
Mom.</i>

180
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:12,367
<i>There's really something
different about you.</i>

181
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:16,933
<i>Felma, you need those frequent
headaches to get checked.</i>

182
00:12:58,333 --> 00:13:01,800
What you're going through
isn't easy, Manuel.

183
00:13:01,933 --> 00:13:05,267
But don't cling

184
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:10,900
to things that go against
our Christian beliefs.

185
00:13:11,033 --> 00:13:13,700
But I'm desperate
already, Pastor.

186
00:13:13,833 --> 00:13:15,133
I understand.

187
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:20,300
But you can't talk
to Jessica anymore.

188
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:24,400
Her time here on earth is over.

189
00:13:24,533 --> 00:13:27,433
She keeps visiting me
in my dreams.

190
00:13:27,567 --> 00:13:30,633
It feels like she wants
to tell me something.

191
00:13:30,767 --> 00:13:31,700
I'm sorry, Pastor,

192
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:34,733
but just like I told Alice...

193
00:13:35,767 --> 00:13:36,900
I won't stop

194
00:13:37,033 --> 00:13:40,600
until I find a way to talk
to my daughter.

195
00:13:57,133 --> 00:13:59,867
Noah... Noah...

196
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:02,600
Noah...

197
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:25,067
Hello, Felma?

198
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,900
Noah.

199
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:28,267
Noah...

200
00:14:28,433 --> 00:14:29,867
What's wrong?

201
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,933
Can we talk?

202
00:14:32,067 --> 00:14:33,167
Okay, I'll come to your house.

203
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:35,633
No, let's just meet

204
00:14:35,767 --> 00:14:37,700
- at the office.
- Ma'am?

205
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:39,233
Oh my...

206
00:14:39,367 --> 00:14:41,267
that's why you're taking
forever.

207
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:43,333
You're still chit-chatting here.

208
00:14:43,467 --> 00:14:45,333
The kids are waiting downstairs.

209
00:14:45,467 --> 00:14:47,467
They're hungry already, Ma'am.

210
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:50,100
Yes, Didang, I'll follow.

211
00:14:50,233 --> 00:14:51,467
Come down soon, Ma'am, okay?

212
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:21,067
It hurts.

213
00:15:32,167 --> 00:15:33,700
It hurts!

214
00:15:35,433 --> 00:15:37,233
I understand you.

215
00:15:37,367 --> 00:15:40,500
But what you're doing is a sin.

216
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:46,000
It's written in the Holy Book

217
00:15:46,133 --> 00:15:49,933
that we're forbidden from
speaking to the dead.

218
00:15:50,067 --> 00:15:52,433
Because the devil will use it.

219
00:15:53,433 --> 00:15:56,700
He'll use the chance
to deceive us.

220
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:59,100
Do you want to be fooled
by the devil?

221
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:04,600
Or let the devil
use your daughter?

222
00:16:04,733 --> 00:16:05,933
No, Pastor.

223
00:16:07,033 --> 00:16:08,133
No.

224
00:16:09,167 --> 00:16:13,133
That's why, Manuel, I know
you love Jessica so much.

225
00:16:13,267 --> 00:16:19,033
But you need to let her go,
let her rest.

226
00:16:19,167 --> 00:16:21,067
If you miss her...

227
00:16:22,033 --> 00:16:25,200
just pray and hold on

228
00:16:25,333 --> 00:16:28,667
to all your beautiful
memories together.

229
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:35,833
Arjun, cancel my appointment.

230
00:16:36,967 --> 00:16:38,067
Sir?

231
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:41,767
You're meeting Mr. Neri.

232
00:16:41,933 --> 00:16:43,633
It's hard to get
a schedule with him.

233
00:16:46,567 --> 00:16:47,933
Just cancel it, okay?

234
00:16:49,433 --> 00:16:51,233
When it comes to Miss Felma...

235
00:16:52,367 --> 00:16:53,967
you drop everything.

236
00:16:55,167 --> 00:16:58,233
You really love her,
even if she didn't choose you.

237
00:16:58,367 --> 00:16:59,833
We're just friends, Arjun.

238
00:17:01,900 --> 00:17:03,667
And she made that clear.

239
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:07,600
But it is not something
a friend does, Sir...

240
00:17:08,567 --> 00:17:10,667
the way you worry about her.

241
00:17:11,867 --> 00:17:13,600
Are you still hoping, Sir,

242
00:17:13,733 --> 00:17:16,867
she'll change her mind?
That you'll get back together?

243
00:17:22,767 --> 00:17:25,433
Thank you so, so much,
Pastor Ishma.

244
00:17:25,567 --> 00:17:27,333
Oh, don't mention it.

245
00:17:27,467 --> 00:17:28,833
Just remember what I said, okay?

246
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:32,533
Guide Manuel.

247
00:17:32,667 --> 00:17:34,533
Remind him to keep praying.

248
00:17:35,633 --> 00:17:37,300
Sure, Pastor, thank you.

249
00:17:51,467 --> 00:17:53,133
- Alice.
- Ah, friend.

250
00:17:53,267 --> 00:17:54,133
Who was that?

251
00:17:54,267 --> 00:17:56,133
Just a pastor I know.

252
00:17:57,133 --> 00:17:58,100
I was gone for a moment,

253
00:17:58,233 --> 00:17:59,767
and so much had already
happened at home.

254
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:01,533
Last time it was a psychic.

255
00:18:01,667 --> 00:18:03,200
Now it's a pastor.

256
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:04,967
Friend, relax.

257
00:18:05,100 --> 00:18:06,000
Come on.

258
00:18:06,133 --> 00:18:08,367
Didn't you tell me
to take care of Manuel?

259
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:09,400
It's handled.

260
00:18:09,533 --> 00:18:11,133
Your secret is safe.

261
00:18:11,267 --> 00:18:14,267
Manuel won't ask about
that dream anymore.

262
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:17,033
And he'll never find out about
your secret with Jessica.

263
00:18:17,167 --> 00:18:18,100
See?

264
00:18:18,233 --> 00:18:20,067
Come on, let's go.

265
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:33,833
- Felma.
- Noah.

266
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:38,267
Ah, didn't you get my text?

267
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:39,500
I said...

268
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:42,133
you could just come later.

269
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:45,700
Felma, I couldn't sit still.

270
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:47,000
What's wrong?

271
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:56,400
I lied to you.

272
00:18:58,967 --> 00:19:00,167
Ah...

273
00:19:01,167 --> 00:19:02,533
The truth is...

274
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:08,300
I'm not okay.

275
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:12,167
It never went away....

276
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:15,300
my headaches.

277
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,267
What?

278
00:19:22,433 --> 00:19:23,500
Yes.

279
00:19:24,967 --> 00:19:26,800
I lied to you.

280
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:30,333
It happened again earlier.

281
00:19:32,767 --> 00:19:33,967
It was so bad.

282
00:19:34,100 --> 00:19:35,700
Like...

283
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:39,167
like my head
was being split open.

284
00:19:40,833 --> 00:19:42,633
That's it, Felma,
we're getting you checked.

285
00:19:43,567 --> 00:19:46,100
That's what I was hoping
to ask you.

286
00:19:47,633 --> 00:19:50,133
I hope you can go with me.

287
00:19:50,267 --> 00:19:52,033
Felma, come on.

288
00:19:52,167 --> 00:19:53,733
You never have to ask me that.

289
00:19:54,867 --> 00:19:56,733
Just tell me when we're leaving.

290
00:19:58,100 --> 00:19:59,300
I'll just be around.

291
00:20:06,867 --> 00:20:07,933
Dear...

292
00:20:10,133 --> 00:20:12,267
I still can't let go.

293
00:20:15,733 --> 00:20:17,567
But Pastor Ishma's right.

294
00:20:19,633 --> 00:20:22,267
I need to let your soul rest.

295
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:27,500
But, dear, keep watching
over me, okay?

296
00:20:28,900 --> 00:20:30,533
And check on me sometimes.

297
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:34,167
Dear...

298
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:35,500
Please whisper to God,

299
00:20:35,667 --> 00:20:38,300
that maybe this pain here...

300
00:20:40,267 --> 00:20:42,900
Maybe he can take
this pain away.

301
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:45,533
Or at least lessen it.

302
00:21:06,533 --> 00:21:09,400
Hello! What is it, Diana?
Why are you calling?

303
00:21:09,567 --> 00:21:13,100
<i> Ma'am Hazel, this is Becca.</i>

304
00:21:13,233 --> 00:21:15,067
Timo's mother.

305
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:17,467
Oh, Becca, why?

306
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:20,900
<i>You still haven't sent
anything to Diana</i>

307
00:21:21,033 --> 00:21:24,500
since Timo took back
his statement.

308
00:21:24,633 --> 00:21:29,133
Wow, you ask for money
as if I owe you something.

309
00:21:29,267 --> 00:21:30,967
I'll send it.

310
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:33,300
But honestly,
I don't even have to.

311
00:21:33,433 --> 00:21:34,833
I already got what I wanted.

312
00:21:34,967 --> 00:21:36,167
And besides, Timo already did

313
00:21:36,300 --> 00:21:37,800
everything I told him to do.

314
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:42,300
Why are you the one calling?

315
00:21:42,467 --> 00:21:45,033
Diana's in the hospital.

316
00:21:45,167 --> 00:21:46,900
She got pneumonia.

317
00:21:47,033 --> 00:21:51,000
She can't be discharged
because we can't pay.

318
00:21:51,133 --> 00:21:53,667
<i> We really have nothing.</i>

319
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:58,233
Could you spare even just enough
for my grandchild's milk?

320
00:21:58,367 --> 00:22:00,700
What happened to the money
I gave Diana

321
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:01,733
to start a small business?

322
00:22:01,867 --> 00:22:02,867
What? She wasted it?

323
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:04,000
<i> No, Ma'am.</i>

324
00:22:04,133 --> 00:22:05,967
She spent it the money

325
00:22:06,100 --> 00:22:08,667
because two of their kids
got sick

326
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:11,233
and were both hospitalized.

327
00:22:11,367 --> 00:22:14,733
Their eldest was confined
for more than a month.

328
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:17,600
We really had nowhere
else to go.

329
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:19,367
You've got so many illnesses.

330
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:20,733
Maybe next time it'll be you.

331
00:22:21,733 --> 00:22:23,433
So you just rely on me?

332
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:26,467
You're taking advantage.

333
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:28,267
I already paid
for Diana's childbirth,

334
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:31,000
and now you still have
the nerve to ask for support?

335
00:22:31,133 --> 00:22:33,400
<i> We really have nothing, Ma'am.</i>

336
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:37,167
We have no one else to turn to.

337
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:40,733
And besides, you and Diana

338
00:22:40,867 --> 00:22:42,833
nd Timo already talked about
this, didn't you?

339
00:22:42,967 --> 00:22:44,767
Well then, wait.

340
00:22:49,733 --> 00:22:50,900
Manuel.

341
00:22:54,533 --> 00:22:55,267
Oh.

342
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:57,367
Why are you suddenly
so worked up?

343
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:58,533
Who were you talking to?

344
00:22:59,667 --> 00:23:01,600
No, it was...

345
00:23:01,733 --> 00:23:02,767
it was Alice.

346
00:23:03,967 --> 00:23:08,033
She said a head nurse
was giving her a hard time.

347
00:23:08,867 --> 00:23:11,500
So I got annoyed, too,
got heated.

348
00:23:11,633 --> 00:23:13,333
Are you done?

349
00:23:13,467 --> 00:23:14,700
Let's go?

350
00:23:26,033 --> 00:23:26,967
<i> You ask for money</i>

351
00:23:27,100 --> 00:23:28,733
<i> as if I owe you something.</i>

352
00:23:29,867 --> 00:23:31,267
<i> I'll give it.</i>

353
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:33,633
<i>But honestly,
I don't even have to.</i>

354
00:23:33,767 --> 00:23:35,100
<i> I already got what I wanted.</i>

355
00:23:35,233 --> 00:23:38,000
<i>Timo already did everything
I told him to do.</i>

356
00:23:46,367 --> 00:23:47,333
Mom?

357
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:53,367
I feel sorry for your wife.

358
00:23:53,500 --> 00:23:54,667
Please forgive me, Mom.

359
00:23:55,567 --> 00:23:56,867
This is my fault.

360
00:23:57,933 --> 00:23:59,933
Why don't you go talk
to Ma'am Hazel?

361
00:24:01,900 --> 00:24:03,100
Sir Manuel?

362
00:24:03,233 --> 00:24:06,100
Becca, please,
I'm begging you.

363
00:24:06,233 --> 00:24:10,133
Please just tell the truth
so I can go back to my family.
